Patch Set 1:

should we have to add a release note here as we are changing the actual size in schema?

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I agree with Abhishek, the fix is good but this needs a release note due to the changes in the schema. Will update to +1 with that.. thanks for looking at this.

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

As it seems to be just the name affected, I'm ok with limiting it to 80 instead of having the db side changed.

We need to document this really well. The test there was nice touch, please add the Reno and flag this out in the metadefs documentation and I think this is very good catch. Thanks.

Patch Set 1:

Do we really need a reno though? The user has never been able to create something with more than 80 characters before due to this bug, so the only end user behavior change is it now will give a more appropriate error than 500.

Release notes certainly don't hurt, but just thinking it's going to say "that thing you couldn't do before - you still can't do it".

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I'm in favor of the release note.  Just something in the "updates" section saying something like:

The metadefs schemas for x, y, z previously specified a "name" element of maximum 255 characters.  An attempt to add a name of greater than 80 characters in length, however, result in a 500 response.  The schemas have been corrected to specify a maximum length of 80 characters.

(Don't bother to include a "fixes" section, I'll do that at release time.)

Patch Set 1:

About my previous comment ... I don't think there is an "updates" section.  Use the "other" section.
Uploaded patch set 2.
